(a_n)_{n\ge1}
\mathbb{R}
\displaystyle B_n=\left\{\sum_{j=n}^{\infty}(\theta_j\cdot a_j)\;:\theta_j\ge 0 \;,\;\sum_{j=n}^{\infty}\theta_j=1\right\}
n\ge1
(b_n)_{n\ge 1}
b_n \in B_n
\forall \;n\ge1
\displaystyle \limsup_{n \to \infty } b_n \le \limsup_{n \to \infty } a_n
n
j \ge n
a_j \le \sup\limits_{m \ge n} a_m
b_n = \sum_{j=n}^\infty \theta_j a_j \le \sum_{j=n}^\infty \theta_j \sup_{m \ge n} a_m = \sup_{m \ge n} a_m
\sup\limits_{m \ge n} a_m
n
n' \ge n
b_{n'} \le \sup\limits_{m\ge n'} a_m \le \sup\limits_{m \ge n} a_m
